    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# DOGE-Adapted Bezier Centerline Extraction\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**HERE Cairo Hackathon 2026 — Problem 1: Centerline Generation**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"This notebook adapts the [DOGE paper](https://arxiv.org/abs/2412.xxxxx) (Differentiable Optimization of Bezier Graph)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for road centerline extraction from GPS traces (VPD + HPD/Probe data).\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Pipeline Overview\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Data Loading** — Load VPD/HPD traces, clip to Kosovo bbox, project to UTM\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Rasterization** — Convert GPS traces into a density segmentation mask\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Tiling** — Split into overlapping 512x512 tiles\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **DOGE Optimization** — Per-tile: alternate TopoAdapt (topology) + DiffAlign (geometry)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **Stitching** — Merge tile results, snap boundary nodes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"6. **Export & Evaluate** — Output centerlines as GPKG, evaluate against ground truth\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 0. Setup & Dependencies\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {\n",
    "    \"ExecuteTime\": {\n",
    "     \"end_time\": \"2026-02-11T15:23:28.560704Z\",\n",
    "     \"start_time\": \"2026-02-11T15:23:26.848446Z\"\n",
    "    }\n",
    "   },\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
